        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        Amazon Customer
        5 Stars
        You have to order this!
        I saw this around Christmas time on ticktock so I got on Amazon and ordered two with the intent to use them both as prizes in the Saran plastic wrap ball game we do on Christmas Eve with grown kids and grandkids. When they came, I opened one and the next thing I knew my husband and I both were obsessed with it So I only wrapped ONE of them into the huge plastic ball filled with prizes and we kept the other one.The booklet gives so many puzzles to attempt to solve, but on ticktock there are videos where you shake a single piece and see where it lands and build the puzzle from there. You wont ever get them all solved.We are Gen X so something about this reminded us of the days of rubics cube and mind bender games of our youth. To my surprise a few of the Gen z age at the house argued over who wanted the other one when it fell out of the plastic ball as a prize.My husband and I pick this game up a few nights a week, solving a puzzle. It breaks the habit of having a phone in your hand, it allows you to LOOK at something and actually touch the puzzle trying to solve it without the glare of the phone games everyone has gotten too use to playing. Definitely gonna be a go to gift for us to give others.

        The game is incredibly fun and addictive. If you have ADHD or are Nuro divergent youre going to love hyper fixating on this awesome and challenging game. It almost seems like a fidget to me in a way.

        If you love a good mind game and you want to be challenged, youre gonna love the different puzzles in this book that comes with the game.         Jennifer Elizabeth Hlavaty
        5.0 out of 5 stars One of the best puzzle games ever!
        Reviewed in the United States on April 3, 2024
        Verified Purchase
        The media could not be loaded.
         Tempted by the low price, compact size, and colorful pieces, I bought this game to add a little variety to my sons' Easter Basket. Little did I know, such a small package would steal the show! Kanoodle has gone nearly everywhere my son (11 years old) has for the past 3 days. Anytime he has a few minutes, he'll whip this out and solve some puzzles; he's particularly fond of the 3D puzzles, his only criticism being that there are fewer of those than the 2D puzzles in this version.

        I feel that this little game is engaging for people of all ages. For myself, I prefer the 2D puzzles...but to be honest, I haven't been able to get my hands on them much...yet ;). While the box is sturdy, the hinges need to be aligned just so for the box to fully close, which may be a bit frustrating for younger kids. If it ever becomes too much of an issue, I plan to throw a rubber band around the box for added security. I would probably do this for traveling as well. Just in case.

        My son created a video showing the completion of the first 3D puzzle and wrote the following review:

        "Very fun, very great for playing in the car. Quite mobile compared to most other games. Absolutely great, love it. However, it would be nice if there where more 3D puzzles, but with the number of ones they have, they will last you some time. Buy it. Now."

        In summary : We recommend Kanoodle highly for it's fun puzzles, colorful parts, and convenient portable case and will likely be checking out some of the other versions soon!

Anytime he has a few minutes, he'll whip this out and solve some puzzles; he's particularly fond of the 3D puzzles, his only criticism being that there are fewer of those than the 2D puzzles in this version.

        I feel that this little game is engaging for people of all ages. For myself, I prefer the 2D puzzles...but to be honest, I haven't been able to get my hands on them much...yet ;). While the box is sturdy, the hinges need to be aligned just so for the box to fully close, which may be a bit frustrating for younger kids. If it ever becomes too much of an issue, I plan to throw a rubber band around the box for added security. I would probably do this for traveling as well. Just in case.

        My son created a video showing the completion of the first 3D puzzle and wrote the following review:

        "Very fun, very great for playing in the car. Quite mobile compared to most other games. Absolutely great, love it. However, it would be nice if there where more 3D puzzles, but with the number of ones they have, they will last you some time. Buy it. Now."

        In summary : We recommend Kanoodle highly for it's fun puzzles, colorful parts, and convenient portable case and will likely be checking out some of the other versions soon!
